added.title: TV Knight 6
added.description: Batman is forced to go to the department store with Alfred, but runs off to watch TV with Commissioner Gordon.

added.title: TV Knight 4
added.description: Batman and Commissioner Gordon go camping but instead of fun outdoor activities they'd rather watch TV.

added.title: TV Knight 5
added.description: Batman pretends to be sick to avoid work so he and Commissioner Gordon can run around town watching their favorite shows.

added.title: TV Knight
added.description: Batman and Commissioner Gordon check in on various happenings around Jump City.

added.title: NBTS 1: Chapter One
added.description: Cyborg becomes trapped in the alternate reality of Night Begins to Shine with a Dragon who wants to steal the song for his own evil purposes.

added.title: NBTS 1: Chapter Two
added.description: Without Cyborg, Beast Boy feels lost and sets out to find himself, but ends up meeting a music legend.

added.title: NBTS 1: Chapter Three
added.description: The Titans return to the alternate reality to save Cyborg but will they be able to defeat the Dragon?

added.title: NBTS 1: Chapter Four
added.description: In a final epic battle, the Titans and their musician friends square off against the Dragon for control of The Night Begins to Shine.

added.title: TV Knight 2
added.description: Batman and Commissioner Gordon have a slumber party and watch their favorite TV shows.

added.title: TV Knight 3
added.description: Batman is more interested in watching TV than participating in his birthday party.

added.title: Fall Anthology
added.description: In an attempt to finish a school project, Craig remembers some of his favorite Fall moments.

added.title: Afterschool Snackdown
added.description: Craig enters a food competition in the Creek but worries he may be out of his league.

added.title: Creature Feature
added.description: Craig finds himself being chased by a monster in the Creek that's straight out of the movies!

added.title: King of Camping
added.description: The Williams Family goes camping and Craig helps his dad prove he's the King of Camping.

added.title: The Rise and Fall of the Green Poncho
added.description: Craig tries to warn his friends about the Other Side of the Creek with a tale from the Creek's defender - the Green Poncho.

added.title: Capture The Flag Part I
added.description: When mysterious circumstances cause issues at the Trading Tree, Craig tries to save the day!

added.title: Capture The Flag Part II
added.description: The Creek gets help from an unlikely friend.

added.title: Capture The Flag Part III
added.description: Craig goes in search of answers, and finds a legend.

added.title: Capture The Flag Part IV
added.description: Craig puts a plan into motion to save the Creek.

added.title: Capture The Flag Part V
added.description: It all comes down to this, the fate of the Creek is at stake!

added.title: Mystery 101
added.description: Velma's got an interview at the prestigious Kingston University, the most selective school in the country. The only catch? The dean wants her and the rest of the Scooby gang to figure out why the ghost of Elias Kingston, the school's founder, is haunting Kingston's book-filled halls!

added.title: Game of Chicken
added.description: Fred gets a call for help from Chuck, his daredevil of a best friend, leading the gang on a rescue mission deep in the caverns of an ancient civilization. Once there, they learn of the real mystery: the ghost of the Tribal Warrior still protects the cavern from outsiders!

added.title: All Paws on Deck
added.description: The gang climb aboard the cruise ship run by Fred's cousin, despite Velma's strong dislike of water. But a water phobia is the least of their problems when a terrifying sea monster attacks the ship!

added.title: Poodle Justice
added.description: It's Scooby's dream come true as the gang visits the set of his favorite TV show and he meets the star, his celebrity crush, a dog actress who plays a detective on the screen. Now all Scooby has to do is work up the courage to actually talk to her while also solving the mystery of the monstrous gargoyle attacking the production!

added.title: Grand Scam
added.description: Shaggy takes the Gang to the Minor League Baseball stadium of his youth only to learn that it's about to be shut down because a Ghostly Baseball Player is scaring away the fans and the team! Shaggy puts aside his cowardly ways to saves his home team but will Scooby stand by his, now not so scared, pal?

added.title: Trading Chases
added.description: Fred switches places with Jeff, the tour guide at a history museum, to give him a chance to lead the gang in solving a mystery. The mystery: a frightening Egyptian crocodile deity is terrorizing the museum. The problem: Fred is instantly jealous of this new guy and sets out to solve the mystery before he can, using Jeff's tour group of children!

added.title: Be Quiet Scooby-Doo!
added.description: To solve the mystery of a creepy crystal crawler, a bat-like cave monster, the gang must venture into the Crystal Canopy, a labyrinth of intricate crystal formations. To make things worse, they can't speak a word while in the Canopy because even the slightest sound will bring the crystals crashing down around them!

added.title: Party Like It's 1899
added.description: Daphne brings the gang to a Victorian murder mystery party, so they can dress up and solve a fake mystery for once. But when an actual headless count starts actually kidnapping people, the gang must stay in character as they tackle the real caper!

added.title: Screama Donna
added.description: To solve the mystery of a ghostly performer haunting her former venue, the gang has to pretend to be a rock band themselves! But can they solve the case before Velma has to actually get on stage and sing?

added.title: Kitchen Frightmare
added.description: Shaggy and Scooby's favorite chef is finally opening his own restaurant but a monstrous Yeti threatens the opening night. The gang has to solve the mystery before dessert is served and Shaggy and Scooby have to resist eating all the food that's meant for the customers!

added.title: What a Night for a Dark Knight!
added.description: When Scooby and the gang come to Gotham City to visit Alfred Pennyworth, they stumble into a dangerous mystery! Alfred's been kidnapped by the Man-Bat! Batman is on the case and he does not want any help from our meddling kids.

added.title: Elementary, My Dear Shaggy!
added.description: When Scooby and the gang are taking a tour of merry old London, they run afoul of horrible screaming skulls of English legend! They team up with an eccentric man who claims to be none other than Sherlock Holmes. Of course, he can't be the real thing, can he?

added.title: A Mystery Solving Gang Divided!
added.description: Scooby-Doo and the gang travel to Chambersburg, a battlefield near Gettysburg, to investigate the mysterious appearance of ghost zombie Civil War soldiers and come face to face with a rival mystery solving gang, the Funky Phantom crew. The rivalry between the two gangs gets so out of hand that it threatens to keep either group from solving the mystery, until the ghost of Abraham Lincoln appears and tries to get them focused.

added.title: Revenge of the Swamp Monster!
added.description: Scooby-Doo and the Mystery Inc. gang meet up with basketball legend and bowling aficionado Chris Paul at a golf tournament fundraiser held in Florida. Shaggy's come to caddy for Mr. Paul and help him with this game so the Assist King can save a local school from going under. But, when a horrible Swamp Monster attacks trying to destroy the charity event, our heroes and Mr. Paul must finish the tournament and save the school, and possibly their own lives!

added.title: Peebles' Pet Shop of Terrible Terrors!
added.description: Scooby and the Mystery Inc. gang meet Wanda Sykes, who is helping save a bunch of cute, fuzzy animals up for adoption in a large pet supply store. When a crazy monster egg hatches a monster in the pet store's back room, our heroes and Wanda must not only save the store and the animals, but their own lives!

added.title: The Scooby of a Thousand Faces!
added.description: When a marble statue comes to life at a museum in Greece, our gang is caught between a braying minotaur and a sword-wielding Wonder Woman! Teaming up with the Amazonian princess from Themyscira, the Mystery Inc. gang experiences a little rift of boys versus girls. Who can solve this mystery better?

added.title: Ollie Ollie In-Come Free!
added.description: When our mystery solving gang agrees to help Ricky Gervais with a haunted antique Egyptian statue of a cat, they find themselves embroiled in a confrontation with the ancient goddess Bast in mummy form!

added.title: The Cursed Cabinet of Professor Madds Markson!
added.description: When our mystery solving gang accepts the invitation to spend one night in the haunted Savannah Hotel in Las Vegas before its controlled demolition, they find that they're not alone. Famous magicians and entertainers Penn and Teller have also accepted the challenge. The winner gets a million bucks. While the loser may not make it out alive because the place is cursed and haunted by the ghost of infamous illusionist Professor Madds Markson and his horrible monster!

added.title: Attack of the Weird Al-Osaurus!
added.description: Driving through the Rocky Mountains, the Mystery Inc. gang discovers a sleep-away accordion camp run by none other than Weird Al Yankovic! But there is no accordion joy when a horrible dinosaur attacks the camp. Can our heroes and Weird Al solve this prehistoric mystery or are they destined to become dino-food?

added.title: When Urkel-Bots Go Bad!
added.description: When Steve Urkel enlists the help of our mystery solving gang to track down the rampaging Urkel-Bot, they stumble onto a deeper mystery. It seems the Urkel-Bot has gone haywire and escaped a Chicago Museum! The mystery deepens with the appearance of a Technomancer, controlling all the robots! Can our gang and Urkel survive an onslaught of the Technomancer's angry robots? And, more importantly, can our gang survive Urkel?

added.title: What a Night for a Knight
added.description: Scooby-Doo and Shaggy stumble across a lone suit of black armor and embark on a quest to find the artifact's missing owner.

added.title: A Clue for Scooby-Doo
added.description: Scooby and the gang become mixed up in a mystery when he surfs into what appears to be the ghost of Captain Cutler.

added.title: Hassle in the Castle
added.description: The sleuths shipwreck on a deserted island and explore a haunted castle.

added.title: Mine Your Own Business
added.description: The gang explores a mining town and investigate a phantom miner, who's driving the business away from a nearby dude ranch.

added.title: Decoy for a Dognapper
added.description: Scooby impersonates a prize-winning Great Dane to catch whoever is stealing show dogs.

added.title: What the Hex Is Going On?
added.description: When the gang visits the Weatherby estate, they must investigate a mysterious voice and a ghost who demands the family return its fortune to a neighboring clan.

added.title: Never Ape an Ape Man
added.description: The gang is hired by Daphne's uncle, a famous director, as extras in his latest project. But the star of the show is a real nasty ape.

added.title: Foul Play in Funland
added.description: The gang investigates a haunted seaside amusement park.

added.title: The Backstage Rage
added.description: A sinister puppet master manipulates the gang's investigation of a case of counterfeit.

added.title: Bedlam in the Big Top
added.description: A ghost clown haunts a small circus, using hypnotism to bend locals to his will.

added.title: Beware the Beast from Below
added.description: Crystal Cove may be the most haunted town in the world but that doesn't stop Scooby and the gang from trying to prove that most of its most famous tourist attractions were fakes, much to the anger and dwindling profits of their parents. But when a radioactive barrel is accidentally opened releasing a hideous sewer beast that cocoons its victims in frozen yogurt, their mystery-solving skills are put to the test. After all, what could a sewer beast, a delicious edible dessert, underground caves and shrimping boats made of balloons possibly have in common? I'll give you a little hint - the local bank.

added.title: The Creeping Creatures
added.description: A long time ago, there was a town called Gatorburg, where gators flowed wild and free and people got rich. Now, it's a ghost town. Gators are all dried up. But when Scooby and the gang receive an imitation Gatorburg purse, they decide to see for themselves if the gators really are gone. Forced to stay overnight when someone steals the engine to the Mystery Machine, they soon discover that gators have indeed returned - only these have comb-overs, walk on two legs and don't like visitors.

added.title: The Secret of the Ghost Rig
added.description: A mysterious ghost trucker is terrorizing Crystal Cove. Add to that all the doorknobs have begun to disappear from around town, someone has hidden a priceless diamond and Fred's dad, the Mayor, is up for re-election against a guy named Avocados. Scooby and the gang have their hands full. Oh, and did we mention Daphne has been set-up on a blind date with a pinhead named Rung Ladderton, who - wait for it - sells ladders for a living.

added.title: Revenge of the Man Crab
added.description: While hosting a volleyball tournament for Trickell's Triquid diet moisture, a smooth drinking beverage just like water except not so fatty, Crystal Cove beach finds itself attacked by a hideous man crab, who has taken a liking to the tournament's female players. Desperate to stop this beast before it scares away all the tourists, the gang investigates convinced it is a disgruntled local named Skipper Shelton, famous for his delicious clam filled waffle cones, his missing nose and his hatred for Crystal Cove bureaucrats. But when Daphne is captured by the Man Crab, Scooby and the gang have to put the mystery solving into overdrive or risk losing not only Daphne but the sanity of their leader Fred, who is not taking the abduction well.

added.title: The Song of Mystery
added.description: A hideous creature named Que Horrifico is turning the children of Crystal Cove in to monsters. The adults in the town are in shock, reacting in the only way they know how, by abandoning their children and running away like cowards. Only Scooby and the gang stay behind to solve the mystery. Going undercover as a family - "Dad" Fred, "Mom" Daphne, "Grandma" Velma, "Son" Shaggy and "Baby" Scooby - the gang rents a house in order to capture Que Horrifico. But when their plan backfires and Que Horrifico uses his power over the monster children to cause them to attack the gang, it looks like all is lost. That is until a cartoon character named Broccoli Head comes to their rescue.

added.title: The Legend of Alice May
added.description: There's a new girl at Crystal Cove High named Alice May and she's set her romantic sights on Fred. Only one problem, Alice is dead! That's right, Fred's new girlfriend is a dead girl. Alice is a ghost, famous for snatching up guys like Fred and disappearing with them forever. Now, she wants to take Fred to the prom, which means he's next. Fortunately, Daphne also wants to go to the prom with Fred and she's not going to let Alice beat her to the "punch" bowl (wink-wink). And what about the rest of the gang? Well, they've got problems of their own. See, Velma wants to go the prom with Shaggy but Scooby wants Shaggy to watch a Vincent Van Ghoul marathon with him. You keeping up? Good because this one is going to get nasty and when it's over, Scooby and the gang will never be the same again.

added.title: In Fear of the Phantom
added.description: Velma's favorite band, the Hex Girls, is in town and the gang has a front row seat. Unfortunately, so does an evil specter named The Phantom, who wants the Hex Girls out of the music business permanently! Solution? Send Daphne undercover as Crush, the newest member of the band. But when she's nabbed by the Phantom, Fred goes into freakout mode finally realizing he actually has feelings for Daphne. Meanwhile, Scooby and Shaggy are having their own problems due to Shaggy spending too much time with Velma. His solution: replace Shaggy with a puppet.

added.title: The Grasp of the Gnome
added.description: The Royal Knights Faire has come to Crystal Cove and the whole gang is in attendance. Unfortunately, so is a scary gnome who has begun attacking and paralyzing guests. Specifically, guests who are wearing pirate costumes. The gang decides to help trap the gnome. But when Shaggy, who is dressed as a pirate along with Scooby, is captured by the frightening little beast, it quickly becomes a race against time to find him or Scooby could lose his best buddy forever.

added.title: Battle of the Humungonauts
added.description: A pair of brutal gargantuas begin breaking apart the town, which sadly mirrors the fractured relationship of Mystery Inc. See, while searching for Shaggy, Scooby accidentally discovers him canoodling with Velma. Feeling betrayed, Scooby is inconsolable despite the best efforts of Fred and Daphne to cheer him up and put the team back together. Although they ultimately reunite to capture and defeat the Humongonauts, the rift in the gang is deep and the question by the end of the episode soon becomes can Mystery Inc. ever be healed again?

added.title: Howl of the Fright Hound
added.description: After a horrible, mechanized beast begins attacking the town, all fingers begin pointing at Scooby. Before the gang can clear his name, the Sheriff has Scooby hauled away to the Crystal Cove Hospital for Criminally Insane Animals. Now, it's up to the gang to clear Scooby's good name. But standing in their way is a new enemy they hadn't counted on: a diabolical parrot named Professor Pericles, who knows more about Mystery Inc. than he should. Add to this the growing friction between Shaggy, Velma and Scooby, and you have a recipe for disaster.

added.title: Stick Hockey
added.description: After Benson unjustifiably throws out Mordecai and Rigby's stick hockey table, he feels guilty and tries to help them get it back.

added.title: Bet to Be Blonde
added.description: Rigby wins a bet with Mordecai and makes him get a blonde perm.

added.title: Skips Strikes
added.description: Skips reveals himself to be an excellent bowler, until he realizes he has to bowl Death's team.

added.title: In the House
added.description: Rigby eggs the wrong house and gets cursed by a wizard.

added.title: Camping Can Be Cool
added.description: Mordecai tries to prove to Margaret that camping is cool.

added.title: Slam Dunk
added.description: Mordecai needs access to the computer so he and Rigby challenge Muscle Man and High Five Ghost to a basketball game for a week's worth of computer time.

added.title: Cool Bikes
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want cool bikes because if their bikes are cool, then they are cool.

added.title: House Rules
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby are sick of Benson's house rules and want to live without them.

added.title: Rap It Up
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby don't want Pops to be called a loser so they say that they'll join him in a rap battle.

added.title: Fancy Restaurant
added.description: Muscle Man has to impress his girlfriend's parents at a fancy dinner.

added.title: Criss Cross Crisis
added.description: Another one of the Professor's plans goes awry when he tries to switch apples for oranges causing the entire town to switch from one body to another. The girls must remedy the situation.

added.title: The Powerpuff Girls Best Rainy Day Adventure Ever/Just Desserts
added.description: The Powerpuff Girls Best Rainy Day Adventure Ever: It's raining in Townsville and there is no crime or villainy afoot. So the girls must stay inside and come up with their very own Powerpuff adventure./Just Desserts: The Smith Family is back and they want revenge. Harold, Maryanne and the kids become a super villain team and make it their goal to destroy the perfect Powerpuff family.

added.title: Speed Demon/Mojo Jonesin'
added.description: Mojo Jonesin':  When the children of Pokey Oaks become envious of the girls' superpowers, a mysterious figure offers them Chemical X. Now, the girls must fight their own classmates who have powers equal to their own./Speed Demon: The girls accidentally fly at the speed of light and when they arrive home, everything has changed. Fifty years have passed and the world has been taken over by Him.

added.title: Town and Out/Child Fearing
added.description: Town and Out: When the Professor gets a new job, the girls have to move away from Townsville. They try to make the best of it but it's just not the same. In fact, it's downright awful./Child Fearing: When the Mayor needs someone to babysit the girls for him, Mojo is unwittingly drafted. Little does Mojo know, taking care of three little girls can be a big hassle.

added.title: Imaginary Fiend/Cootie Gras
added.description: Imaginary Fiend: The new boy in school has a special friend nobody else can see. When this imaginary friend begins destroying the class, the girls must imagine how to stop him./Cootie Gras: Mojo observes that everyone is staying away from little Harry Pitt because he has cooties. So Mojo concocts a plan to keep the girls away by using this cootie-covered boy as bait.

added.title: Bubblevision/Bought and Scold
added.description: Bubblevision: Bubbles' fighting has been really terribly lately and the Professor discovers she needs glasses. Bubbles is humiliated by these huge, horrible things and never wants to see or be seen again./Bough and Scold: When Princess buys Townsville, she makes crime legal. Now, the girls have nothing to do and the town is in shambles.

added.title: Twisted Sister/Cover Up
added.description: Twisted Sister: The girls decide they need some help fighting crime so they create another Powerpuff Girl. But they don't get the combination of sugar, spice and everything nice quite right./Cover Up: Blossom and Bubbles learn that Buttercup has secretly been rubbing a security blanket before every battle to make herself a super fighter. Can the girls convince Buttercup that her strength is within?

added.title: Mo Job/Pet Feud
added.description: Mo Job: Princess hires Mojo to devise the perfect plan to destroy the girls, who are quite shocked when they find Princess has powers equal to their own./Pet Feud: The Professor creates the perfect little pet. But there's only one catch: he can only be fed once a day. When the girls each feed him, they find that their sweet little friend has become a wild beast!

added.title: A Cranky Goodbye
added.description: When Bulstrode excitedly announces that he is getting a brand new paint job on the Mainland, everyone is thrilled for him -- except for a crankier-than-usual Cranky. When the crane's dismissive comments upset Bulstrode, the tugboat storms off, leaving Thomas and Percy to pick up the pieces, repair their friendship, and encourage both of them to do something they have never done before -- talk about their true feelings towards each other!
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go
